Always enjoy the zhi cha version of vegetarian food from this stall. I think their pricing is reasonable with above average food quality.

The dishes I ordered today is meant for 4 male adult, and in quantity wise itâ€™s more than enough for all to have a filling lunch.

The curry fish head and vinegar pork trotter is also one of my regular dishes.

Very generous portion for the price.  I always think that vegetarian food is very expensive but this stall changed my mind. Food option is good - wide variety. The only thing ðŸ‘Ž food is very very very oily.
Minus 1 star for this.

Nice vegetarian food in the quiet neighbourhood area. This stall is in a coffee shop in front of Dunman school.

The chili chicken rice very delicious, can smell the wokhey in the dishes.

The rice that they use also fluffy and soft.

I noticed that in store menu donâ€™t have creamy chicken rice and lemon chicken rice like shown in grab food menu.
Had mala hotpot for the first time and I must say that the delicacy is now my favourite.
Very delicious vegetarian ala carte dishes!
